ps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Volume#cite_note-23"><span class=3D"cite-bracket=
">[</span>22<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup></li>
<li>The <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Volumetric_flow_rate" titl=
e=3D"Volumetric flow rate">volumetric flow rate</a> or <a href=3D"https://e=
n.wikipedia.org/wiki/Discharge_(hydrology)" title=3D"Discharge (hydrology)"=
>discharge</a> is the volume of fluid which passes through a given surface =
per unit time.</li>
<li>The <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Volumetric_heat_capacity" =
title=3D"Volumetric heat capacity">volumetric heat capacity</a> is the <a h=
ref=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Heat_capacity" title=3D"Heat capacity"=
>heat capacity</a> of the substance divided by its volume.</li></ul>
